{"title_page": "Cheriyo (film series)", "text_new": "{{short description|Sri Lankan comedy media franchise}}\n{{Use mdy  dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox media franchise\n| italic_title = no\n| title = Cheriyo\n| image = \n| caption = \n| creator = [[Roy de Silva]]\n| origin = ''[[Cheriyo Doctor]]'' (1991)\n| owner = \n| films = [[#Films|List of films]]\n| soundtracks = ''[[#Soundtracks|See below]]''\n}}\n\n'''''Cheriyo''''' is a Sri Lankan [[film series]] centered on a series of [[comedy]] [[action film]]s, produced by TK Films and RS Films and distributed by EAP cinema theaters.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://archives.sarasaviya.lk/2014/12/11/?fn=sa14121125 |title=Sinhala screened films |publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=23 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2015/04/23/?fn=sa15042318 |title=Sri Lankan Screened Films |publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://archives.sarasaviya.lk/2015/05/14/?fn=sa15051428 |title=Sinhala screened films |publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=23 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2015/09/24/?fn=sa15092427 |title=Sri Lankan Screened Films |publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=11 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161009011501/http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2015/09/24/?fn=sa15092427 |archive-date=9 October 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Overview==\nThe franchise consists of four films in the ''Cheriyo'' series, ''[[Cheriyo Doctor]]'' (1991), ''[[Cheriyo Captain]]'' (1995), ''[[Cheriyo Darling]]'' (1996) and ''[[Cheriyo Holman]]'' (2002). The first three films of the franchise was directed by [[Roy de Silva]] with his screenplay and dialogues. The film [[Cheriyo Doctor|''Cheriyo'' ''Doctor'']] was produced by Thilak Atapattu for TK Films, cinematography by S. A. Gafoor and edited by S. V. Chandran.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.films.lk/cheriyo-doctor-sinhala-film-1477.html |title=Cheriyo Doctor - \u0da0\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0ddd \u0da9\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dca\u0da7\u0dbb\u0dca |publisher=Sinhala Cinema Database |accessdate=23 December 2017}}</ref> The second film [[Cheriyo Captain|''Cheriyo'' ''Captain'']] was produced again by Thilak Atapattu, cinematography by G. Nandasena and edited by Densil Jayaweera.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.films.lk/cheriyo-captain-sinhala-film-1574.html |title=Cheriyo Captain - \u0da0\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0ddd \u0d9a\u0dd0\u0db4\u0dca\u0da7\u0db1\u0dca |publisher=Sarasaviya |accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref> Third film [[Cheriyo Darling|''Cheriyo'' ''Darling'']] was co-produced by director [[Roy de Silva]] with his wife [[Sumana Amarasinghe]] for Roy-Sumana Films (RS Films). The film cinematography done by J.J. Yogaraja and edited by Densil Jayaweera.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.films.lk/cheriyo-darling-sinhala-film-1598.html |title=Cheriyo Darling - \u0da0\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0ddd \u0da9\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca |publisher=Sinhala Cinema Database |accessdate=23 December 2017}}</ref> The final film of the franchise, [[Cheriyo Holman|''Cheriyo'' ''Holman'']] was directed by Parakrama Jayasinghe and co-produced by Raj Ranasinghe and Thilak Atapattu. Cinematography by G. Nandasena and edited by M. S. Aliman. All four films were music directed by [[Somapala Rathnayake]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.films.lk/cheriyo-holman-sinhala-film-1852.html |title=Cheriyo Holman - \u0da0\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0ddd \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dca\u0db8\u0db1\u0dca |publisher=Sinhala Cinema Database |accessdate=23 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:16%;\" | Film\n! SL release date\n! Director(s)\n! Producer(s)\n! Story by\n! Composer(s)\n! Status\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background:#CCCCFF;\" | ''Cheriyo'' series\n|-\n! ''[[Cheriyo Doctor]]''\n| October 11, 1991 \n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Roy de Silva]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" | Thilak Atapattu\n| rowspan=\"3\" | Roy de Silva\n| rowspan=\"4\" | Somapala Rathnayake\n| rowspan=\"4\" | Released <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nfc.gov.lk/films-history.php | title=Sri Lanka Cinema History | publisher=National Film Corporation of Sri Lanka | accessdate=3 October 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n! ''[[Cheriyo Captain]]''\n| October 13, 1995\n|-\n! ''[[Cheriyo Darling]]''\n| October 25, 1996\n| colspan=\"1\" | [[Sumana Amarasinghe]]\n|-\n! ''[[Cheriyo Holman]]''\n| May 24, 2002 <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/020602/tv/TV2.HTML#1 |title=Cheriyo Holman' now |publisher=Sunday Times |accessdate=23 December 2017}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"1\" | Parakrama Jayasinghe\n| colspan=\"1\" | Thilak Atapattu <br> Raj Ranasinghe\n| Clive Martens\n|}\n\n==Timeline==\n<!-- DO NOT CHANGE WITHOUT DISCUSSION -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|+ \n! scope=\"col\" align=\"center\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" align=\"center\" | Feature films\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 1991\n| ''[[Cheriyo Doctor]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 1995\n| ''[[Cheriyo Captain]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 1996\n| ''[[Cheriyo Darling]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2002\n| ''[[Cheriyo Holman]]''\n|}\n\n==Films==\n\n===''Cheriyo Doctor'' (1991)===\n{{main|Cheriyo Doctor}}\n''Cheriyo Doctor'', centering on the incidents occur within a mental hospital run by Professor. Incidents starts when Nurse Surangi falls in love with one of fake patient Chaminda Randenigala. After series of comedy incidents, Chaminda's friend Nalin also attended to the hospital with fake illness and Chaminda's realized that his sister Madhu falls in love with Nalin. However, Chaminda's mother Nayana Randenigala opposes their romantic behaviors and locked Madhu. With the help of hospital staff, Chaminda and Nalin fight against Nayana's thugs and win their fiancees.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rateyourmusic.com/film/\u0da0\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0ddd_\u0da9\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dca\u0da7\u0dbb\u0dca/ |title=\u0da0\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0ddd \u0da9\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0dca\u0da7\u0dbb\u0dca Cheriyo Doctor crew |publisher=Rate Your Music |accessdate=23 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n===''Cheriyo Captain'' (1995)===\n{{main|Cheriyo Captain}}\n''Cheriyo Captain'', centering on the incidents occur between an army group and a guerrilla group. Army group led by Captain Doson commands seven funny soldiers - Huntin, Ping Pong, Bantum, Kang Kung, Pabul, Tom Tom accompany with Tarzan. Guerrilla group led by Alphonsus who kidnap Varuni, only daughter of General Tagore. Captain Doson has informed to rescue Varuni and bring the guerrillas down. Along the course, Varuni's boyfriend Rahal and his friend joined the army troop at the jungle. After series of comedy events, army troop rescued Varuni and meantime destroy the bridge that connect the Army territory and Alphosus territory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sinhalamovies.info/cheriyo-darling-1996-sinhala-movie-watch-online/ |title=Cheriyo Darling \u2013 1996 |publisher=sinhalamovies |accessdate=23 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n===''Cheriyo Darling'' (1996)===\n{{main|Cheriyo Darling}}\n''Cheriyo Darling'', centering on the incidents occur when a popular actress Miss Sweetie attends to the mental hospital run by Professor. All the male workers at the hospital start to flirt around her to win her heart. Meanwhile, Sweetie's boyfriend enters to the hospital with a fake mental illness. However, after series of comedy incidents Gulliver and his henchman rushed to the hospital and looking to kidnap Miss Sweeties. With the final battle initiated by hotel workers, Gulliver flees with his troop and Miss Sweetie joins with her boyfriend and leave the hospital.\n\n===''Cheriyo Holman'' (2002)===\n{{main|Cheriyo Holman}}\n\n''Cheriyo Darling'', centering on the incidents revolve around a hotel. Many people visit to the hotel and reserve their rooms. Meanwhile hotel is haunted by a ghost, \"Mohini\" and every people gets scared with her involvement for horror incidents. However a reveal about the ghost came to know at the last part of the film. Until that moment, the film revolves around many comedy incidents as well as hotel workers flirt around the beautiful girl, later known as the ghost.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\" width=\"100%\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Cast\n! colspan=\"4\" | Film & Character\n|-\n!  width:10%;\"| ''[[Cheriyo Doctor]]'' <br>(1991)\n!  width:10%;\"| ''[[Cheriyo Captain]]'' <br>(1995)\n!  width:10%;\"| ''[[Cheriyo Darling]]'' <br>(1996)\n!  width:10%;\"| ''[[Cheriyo Holman]]'' <br>(2002)\n|-\n! [[Bandu Samarasinghe]]\n| colspan=\"1\" | Marmite\n| colspan=\"1\" | Huntin / Fruit Salad\n| colspan=\"1\" | Marmite\n| colspan=\"1\" | \n|-\n! [[Tennison Cooray]]\n| colspan=\"1\" | Hospital attendant\n| colspan=\"1\" | Bantum\n| colspan=\"1\" | Doctor Dunath Mala\n| colspan=\"1\" | \n|-\n! [[Joe Abeywickrama]]\n| colspan=\"1\" | Professor\n| colspan=\"1\" | Captain Doson\n| colspan=\"1\" | Professor\n| colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|-\n! [[Freddie Silva]]\n| colspan=\"1\" | Doctor Coco / Virindu singer\n| colspan=\"1\" | Ping Pong\n| colspan=\"1\" | Doctor Coco\n| colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|-\n! [[Sumana Amarasinghe]]\n| colspan=\"1\" | Nayana Randenigala\n| colspan=\"1\" | Teena\n| colspan=\"1\" | Madam\n| colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|-\n! Nawanandana Wijesinghe\n| colspan=\"1\" | Patient\n| colspan=\"1\" | Tom Tom\n| colspan=\"1\" | Formalin\n| colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|-\n! Manel Chandralatha\n| colspan=\"1\" | Nurse\n| colspan=\"1\" | Nancy\n| colspan=\"1\" | Nurse\n| colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|-\n! [[Cletus Mendis]]\n| colspan=\"1\" | Cleet\n| colspan=\"1\" | Alphonsus\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|-\n! [[Sanath Gunathilake]]\n| colspan=\"1\" | Chaminda Randenigala\n| colspan=\"1\" | Rahal\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#d3d3d3;\"|\n|-\n! [[Sabeetha Perera]]\n| colspan=\"1\" | Surangi\n| colspan=\"1\" | Varuni\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"ba