{"title_page": "Patricia Bray", "text_new": "{{short description|Romance and fantasy writer}}   \n{{Infobox person\n  | honorific_prefix =   \n  | name             = Patricia Bray  \n  | honorific_suffix =  \n  | image            =   \n  | image_size       =   \n  | alt              =   \n  | caption          =   \n  | native_name      =   \n  | native_name_lang =   \n  | birth_name       =   \n  | birth_date       =    \n  | birth_place      =    \n  | death_date       =   \n  | death_place      =   \n  | nationality      = American  \n  | education        = Master's in IT  \n  | alma_mater       =   \n  | known_for        = Romance and Fantasy Fiction\n  | website = http://www.patriciabray.com/  \n  | notable_works    =[[Devlin's Luck]]}}\n\n'''Patricia Bray ''' is a romance and fantasy writer as well as an IT Project manager and [[Systems Analyst]].\n\n==Biography==\nPatricia Bray lives in [[New England]] where she works in IT and has a master's degree in [[Information Technology]]. She began by writing historical romances set in Regency England. She began a new series of stories which were more epic fantasy in style and scale. Her books have been translated into multiple languages including Russian, German, Portuguese and Hebrew. Her novel ''[[Devlin's Luck]]'' won the [[Compton Crook Award]] in 2003. Bray also works as an editor with a number of anthologies to her name we well as ''After Hours: Tales from the Ur-Bar'' and ''The Modern Fae\u2019s Guide to Surviving Humanity''. She works a lot with [[Joshua Palmatier]].<ref name=\"Fantastic Fiction\">{{cite web | title=Patricia Bray | website=Fantastic Fiction | url=https://www.fantasticfiction.com/b/patricia-bray/ | access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\"PenguinRandomhouse.com 2015\">{{cite web | title=Patricia Bray | website=PenguinRandomhouse.com | date=2015-04-01 | url=https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/authors/35019/patricia-bray | access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\"Bray Reviews\">{{cite web | last=Bray | first=Patricia | last2=Reviews | first2=Complete Book | title=Books by Patricia Bray and Complete Book Reviews | website=PublishersWeekly.com | url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/authorpage/patricia-bray.html | access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\"Author 2013\">{{cite web | author=Author | title=Interview: Author Patricia Bray | website=Odyssey Workshop | date=2013-04-14 | url=https://odysseyworkshop.wordpress.com/2013/04/14/935/ | access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\"House 2011\">{{cite web | last=House | first=Africa | title=Patricia Bray and Joshua Palmatier | website=AfricaResource | date=2011-04-28 | url=https://www.africaresource.com/house/reading-series/117-patricia-bray-and-joshua-palmatier | access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n\n*A London Season (1997)\n*An Unlikely Alliance (1998)\n*Lord Freddie's First Love (1999)\n*The Irish Earl (2000)\n*A Most Suitable Dutchess (2001)\n*The Wrong Mr. Wright (2002)\n*A Most Suitable Duchess (2015)\n\n===Sword of Change===\n*Devlin's Luck (2002)\n*Devlin's Honor (2003)\n*Devlin's Justice (2004)\n\n===Chronicles of Josan===\n*The First Betrayal (2006)\n*The Sea Change (2007)\n*The Final Sacrifice (2008)\n\n===Collection===\n*Bewitching Kittens (1998) (with Janice Bennett and Cathleen Clare)\n\n===As editor===\n*After Hours (2011) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*The Modern Fae's Guide to Surviving Humanity (2012) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*Clockwork Universe: Steampunk vs Aliens (2014) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*Temporally Out of Order (2015) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*Alien Artifacts (2016) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*Were- (2016) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*All Hail Our Robot Conquerors! (2017) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*Second Round (2018) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*Portals (2019) (with S C Butler)\n\n==References and sources==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bray, Patricia}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women writers]]\n[[Category:American fantasy writers]]\n[[Category:Romantic fiction writers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Romance and fantasy writer}}   \n{{Infobox person\n  | honorific_prefix =   \n  | name             = Patricia Bray  \n  | honorific_suffix =  \n  | image            =   \n  | image_size       =   \n  | alt              =   \n  | caption          =   \n  | native_name      =   \n  | native_name_lang =   \n  | birth_name       =   \n  | birth_date       =    \n  | birth_place      =    \n  | death_date       =   \n  | death_place      =   \n  | nationality      = American  \n  | education        = Master's in IT  \n  | alma_mater       =   \n  | known_for        = Romance and Fantasy Fiction\n  | website = http://www.patriciabray.com/  \n  | notable_works    =[[Devlin's Luck]]}}\n\n'''Patricia Bray ''' is a romance and fantasy writer as well as an IT Project manager and [[Systems Analyst]].\n\n==Biography==\nPatricia Bray lives in [[New England]] where she works in IT and has a master\u2019s degree in [[Information Technology]]. She began by writing historical romances set in Regency England. She began a new series of stories which were more epic fantasy in style and scale. Her books have been translated into multiple languages including Russian, German, Portuguese and Hebrew. Her novel ''[[Devlin's Luck]]'' won the [[Compton Crook Award]] in 2003. Bray also works as an editor with a number of anthologies to her name we well as ''After Hours: Tales from the Ur-Bar'' and ''The Modern Fae\u2019s Guide to Surviving Humanity''. She works a lot with [[Joshua Palmatier]].<ref name=\"Fantastic Fiction\">{{cite web | title=Patricia Bray | website=Fantastic Fiction | url=https://www.fantasticfiction.com/b/patricia-bray/ | access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\"PenguinRandomhouse.com 2015\">{{cite web | title=Patricia Bray | website=PenguinRandomhouse.com | date=2015-04-01 | url=https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/authors/35019/patricia-bray | access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\"Bray Reviews\">{{cite web | last=Bray | first=Patricia | last2=Reviews | first2=Complete Book | title=Books by Patricia Bray and Complete Book Reviews | website=PublishersWeekly.com | url=https://www.publishersweekly.com/pw/authorpage/patricia-bray.html | access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\"Author 2013\">{{cite web | author=Author | title=Interview: Author Patricia Bray | website=Odyssey Workshop | date=2013-04-14 | url=https://odysseyworkshop.wordpress.com/2013/04/14/935/ | access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\"House 2011\">{{cite web | last=House | first=Africa | title=Patricia Bray and Joshua Palmatier | website=AfricaResource | date=2011-04-28 | url=https://www.africaresource.com/house/reading-series/117-patricia-bray-and-joshua-palmatier | access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n\n*A London Season (1997)\n*An Unlikely Alliance (1998)\n*Lord Freddie's First Love (1999)\n*The Irish Earl (2000)\n*A Most Suitable Dutchess (2001)\n*The Wrong Mr. Wright (2002)\n*A Most Suitable Duchess (2015)\n\n===Sword of Change===\n*Devlin's Luck (2002)\n*Devlin's Honor (2003)\n*Devlin's Justice (2004)\n\n===Chronicles of Josan===\n*The First Betrayal (2006)\n*The Sea Change (2007)\n*The Final Sacrifice (2008)\n===Collection===\n*Bewitching Kittens (1998) (with Janice Bennett and Cathleen Clare)\n===As editor===\n*After Hours (2011) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*The Modern Fae's Guide to Surviving Humanity (2012) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*Clockwork Universe: Steampunk vs Aliens (2014) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*Temporally Out of Order (2015) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*Alien Artifacts (2016) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*Were- (2016) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*All Hail Our Robot Conquerors! (2017) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*Second Round (2018) (with Joshua Palmatier)\n*Portals (2019) (with S C Butler)\n\n==References and sources==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bray, Patricia}}\n\n[[Category